1.Must include the meta tag in the head:
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

2.Link to bootstrap stylesheet:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-MCw98/SFnGE8fJT3GXwEOngsV7Zt27NXFoaoApmYm81iuXoPkFOJwJ8ERdknLPMO" crossorigin="anonymous">

3.Bootstrap scripts:
<script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-ChfqqxuZUCnJSK3+MXmPNIyE6ZbWh2IMqE241rYiqJxyMiZ6OW/JmZQ5stwEULTy" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

4.Page must be wrapped in a container given one of two classes:
	.container or .container-fluid

	.container provides a fixed width container
	.container-fluid provides a full width container, spanning entire viewport

*Bootstrap uses a 12 column grid system
*Each row is made of a div with the class .row
*Then the columns to span is added in this format:

<div class='row'>
	<div class='col-*-*'></div>
	<div class='col-*-*'></div>
</div>
<div class='row'>
	<div class='col-*-*'></div>
</div>

first * can be one of four sizes (xs, sm, md, lg)

Second * is how many columns to span, this must = 12

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
  <div class="col-sm-8">.col-sm-8</div>
</div>